{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"hasAccess": false, "showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6682bd85ba0e94a3c4025d28", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 1, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 90, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "", "questionLabels": [], "question": {"text": "A convex mirror of radius of curvature <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math> forms an image that is half the size of the object. The object distance is :", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "NRxno", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "fqcpN", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "M1Wbs", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "uDAxi", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>Given\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>So,\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>For convex mirror, virtual image is formed for real object. Thus, magnification\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>m</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>The magnification can be written as</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mi>u</mi></mfrac><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Equation (1) implies that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mi>u</mi></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>\u21d2</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>The relation between the object distance, image distance and the focal length of the mirror is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>f</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>v</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>u</mi></mfrac><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Equation (2) implies that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>15</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>u</mi></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>u</mi></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>\u21d2</mo><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": {"videoId": "e604f8d02c94466f917492c02f95a6b4", "provider": "vdocipher", "thumbnailLight": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/ypn28uYSUEjV5.480.jpeg", "thumbnailDark": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/ypn28uYSUEjV5.480.jpeg", "premiumModules": [{"premiumModuleId": "6628114842d540dfcb148ecb", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "64c7e8e829737784b294e469", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "6788cc0b2dbc1ecacabb7026", "isFree": false}], "description": "JEE Main (Imp. PYQs from 2023 - 2019)"}, "bucket": "Easy Ques (Board Level)", "concepts